President Donald Trump and Vice President Mike Pence met with senior members of the Administration to discuss federal support for Hurricane Irma preparation, response, and recovery, as well as ongoing support for recovery from Hurricane Harvey. The President emphasized the importance of all departments and agencies staying fully engaged in supporting the Governors of the U.S. Virgin Islands, Puerto Rico, Florida, and other affected states, as well as providing assistance to international partners in the storm's path. The President's priority is saving lives and he urged those in the storm's path to follow the instructions of their state and local officials. The President and Vice President expressed their thoughts and prayers for those affected and recognized the efforts of volunteer and faith-based organizations.